# 🐞 Manual Testing Bug Report Project

## 📖 Project Description
This project contains **manual testing bug reports** for a sample **E-commerce Website**.  
The goal of this project is to demonstrate **bug reporting skills** for different modules of a web application.  

The website includes the following modules:
- 🔐 User Authentication (Login/Signup)  
- 🔎 Product Search  
- 🛒 Add to Cart  
- 💳 Checkout & Payment  

---

## 🎯 Scope of Testing
- ✅ Functional Testing  
- 🎨 UI/UX Testing  
- 👥 Usability Testing  
- 🔄 Regression Testing  

---

## 📂 Project Structure

Manual-Testing-Bug-Report-Project/
│
├── README.md
├── Bug_Reports/
│ ├── Bug_Report_Template.md
│ ├── Sample_Bug_Report_Table.xlsx
│ └── Sample_Bug_Report.md
└── Screenshots/


---

## 🐞 Bug Report Template
A standard bug report template is included for consistency.  

```markdown
**Bug ID:** BR-001  
**Module:** Login Page  
**Title:** Login button not working with valid credentials  
**Severity:** High  
**Priority:** P1  
**Environment:** Windows 10, Chrome v115  
**Precondition:** User account already exists  

### Steps to Reproduce
1. Go to Login Page  
2. Enter valid email and password  
3. Click on "Login" button  

### Expected Result
User should be redirected to the dashboard.  

### Actual Result
Nothing happens after clicking on the "Login" button.  

| Bug ID | Module     | Title                                 | Severity | Priority | Status |
| ------ | ---------- | ------------------------------------- | -------- | -------- | ------ |
| BR-001 | Login Page | Login button not working              | High     | P1       | Open   |
| BR-002 | Search     | Search results not displayed properly | Medium   | P2       | Open   |
| BR-003 | Cart       | "Remove from Cart" not removing item  | High     | P1       | Open   |
| BR-004 | Checkout   | Payment page crashes on submit        | Critical | P1       | Open   |
| BR-005 | UI/UX      | Logo alignment issue in header        | Low      | P3       | Open   |

Clone this repository

Open Bug_Reports/ to view bug reports

Use the Bug_Report_Template.md for writing new bugs

Add screenshots in Screenshots/ for better documentation
